Will Lummus is a professional rodeo contestant from Byhalia, Mississippi, who specializes in steer wrestling. He has qualified for the Wrangler National Finals Rodeo (NFR) six times and joined the Professional Rodeo Cowboys Association (PRCA) in 2012.

Lummus has earned numerous major regular-season wins, including victories at the Fort Worth Stock Show & Rodeo, San Angelo Rodeo, Calgary Stampede, Sheridan WYO Rodeo, Ogden Pioneer Days, and Governor’s Cup Rodeo.

Here you can follow Will Lummus’ net worth, career earnings, career, biography, achievements, relationship status, and more.

About Will Lummus

Will Lummus was born into a family with a rich rodeo history. His father, Luke Lummus, was a bull rider, and his Uncle Bob was a four-time NFR contestant.

This early exposure to the rodeo world sparked Lummus’s interest in the sport, setting him on a path to become one of the top steer wrestlers in the professional rodeo circuit.

Early Career

Lummus’s early career was marked by his participation in both high school and college rodeos, which laid the foundation for his successful professional career.

He attended the University of Tennessee at Martin, where he was part of the National Intercollegiate Rodeo Association’s men’s championship team.

Lummus graduated with a bachelor’s degree in exercise science and wellness and later obtained his physical therapy assistant certification.

Professional Career

Lummus’s professional career took off when he joined the Professional Rodeo Cowboys Association (PRCA) in 2012.

Since then, he has consistently qualified for the NFR every year since 2018. Lummus has finished as the Reserve World Champion in steer wrestling for two consecutive years.

In 2021, he secured the NFR Average Title. Lummus’s professional career is also marked by numerous top-notch wins, including at the Coleman PRCA Rodeo and Gladewater Round-Up Rodeo.

In 2023, he entered the NFR in 4th place. He has had major wins at the Fort Worth Stock Show & Rodeo, San Angelo Rodeo, Calgary Stampede, Sheridan WYO Rodeo, Ogden Pioneer Days, and Governor’s Cup Rodeo. His career earnings total over $1,126,411.

Will Lummus’s Net Worth in 2023

As of 2023, Will Lummus’s net worth is estimated to be $3 million.

Career Earnings

In the 2023 regular season, Lummus earned $143,988. His biggest paydays include the Cinch Playoffs Governor’s Cup (South Dakota), where he earned $31,500, and the Fort Worth Stock Show and Rodeo, where he earned $27,080.

Personal Details

Wife

Will Lummus’s wife is Jenna Lummus. She is a pharmacist and also a barrel racer in the Women’s Professional Rodeo Association (WPRA).

The couple got married on October 7, 2017. They currently reside in Byhalia, Mississippi.

How old is Will Lummus?

He is 31 years old, as of 2023.

How tall is he?

He is 6 ft 2 inches tall.

What is his nationality?

He is American.

Career Highlights

  • Career earnings: $1,126,411
  • 2022 world standings place: 2nd
  • 2022 Wrangler NFR standings place: 4th 
  • 2022 Wrangler NFR earnings: $146,408
  • 2022 earnings: $266,188
  • Education: University of Tennessee-Martin
  • Wrangler NFR Average Titles: 1 (2021)
  • Wrangler NFR Qualifications: 5 (2018-22)

2023 Highlights

• Won the Stampede at the Ike (West Monroe, La.)

• Won the Magnolia Center Pro Rodeo (Laurel, Miss.)

• Won the Fort Worth (Texas) Stock Show & Rodeo

• Won the 150th Silver Spurs Rodeo (Kissimmee, Fla.)

• Won the Georgia (Perry) National Rodeo

• Won the Johnson County Sheriff’s Posse Rodeo (Cleburne, Texas)

• Won the Sheridan WYO Rodeo

• Co-champion at the Southeastern Livestock Exposition (Montgomery, Ala.)
